    The resonance region evaluation for 54Fe was initially        2625 1451
    evaluated at IRSN, up to 1.036 MeV, by using SAMMY to fit     2625 1451
    Pandey et al. [1] and Cornelis et al. [2] data. In both cases 2625 1451
    a time of flight correction was applied, accounting for energy2625 1451
    shifts between fits and unmodified data retrieved from EXFOR. 2625 1451
    The evaluation uses the Reich-Moore approximation and the     2625 1451
    LRF=7 format. The initial J and parity assignments of         2625 1451
    resonances were taken from the Atlas of Neutron Resonances.   2625 1451
    As neither Cornelis et al. nor Pandey et al. resolved all     2625 1451
    resonances, the IRSN fits were supplemented with 64 resonances2625 1451
    compiled in the newest edition of the Atlas, measured mostly  2625 1451
    by Giubrone et al. [3]. Even with the addition of these p-    2625 1451
    and d-wave resonances, the average capture cross section      2625 1451
    was substantially lower than the measured average capture     2625 1451
    data of Allen et al. (1976) [4]. We computed the capture      2625 1451
    background from 100 keV-1 MeV by subtracting the group-wise   2625 1451
    cross section determined from the resonance parameters from   2625 1451
    the Allen et al. data. This not only brought the average      2625 1451
    cross section into agreement with Allen et al. [4] data, but  2625 1451
    also with the new Wallner data [5]. To ensure a proper match  2625 1451
    of the fast region capture onto the average resonance region  2625 1451
    capture cross section, we extended our EMPIRE calculations    2625 1451
    to 10 eV and tuned our calculation to match the average data  2625 1451
    of Allen et al. (1976)  [4].                                  2625 1451
    The evaluation compares favorably with Atlas values for both  2625 1451
    the thermal cross sections and resonance integrals, but it    2625 1451
    does not match the KADoNiS-0.3 recommended value for MACS(30  2625 1451
    keV)  [6]. This is because the KADoNiS recommendation was     2625 1451
    based on a preliminary version of the Wallner data.           2625 1451
