 -------------------------                                        2625 1451
                                                                  2625 1451
 MF=33                                                            2625 1451
   Covariances were determined using Kalman filter-inspired       2625 1451
   Bayesian update procedure. This methodology combines           2625 1451
   experimental uncertainties with the model constraints imposed  2625 1451
   through the sensitivity profiles provided by the EMPIRE code.  2625 1451
   Using KALMAN, the model parameters were sequentially adjusted  2625 1451
   to each considered experiment. Cross section covariances are   2625 1451
   obtained by propagating covariances of the model parameters.   2625 1451
   The covariances were computed for the major reaction channels  2625 1451
   represented in the evaluations: total, elastic, inelastic,     2625 1451
   capture, (n, 2n), and (n, p). Inelastic scattering to          2625 1451
   individual discrete levels (MT=51,...,90) and to the continuum 2625 1451
   (MT=91) were combined together into MT=4. In addition,         2625 1451
   covariances for the sum of all the remaining channels (MT=5)   2625 1451
   are provided. Experimental uncertainties reported in EXFOR, if 2625 1451
   available, were used to determine the long-range correlations  2625 1451
   in the experimental covariance matrices. If such information   2625 1451
   was not available 45% correlation between different energy     2625 1451
   points for the same reaction was assumed. The experimental     2625 1451
   datasets showing pronounced fluctuation structure were         2625 1451
   smoothed before being used.                                    2625 1451
                                                                  2625 1451
   The EMPIRE/KALMAN genrated covariances were extended over the  2625 1451
   resonance region. Since actual uncertainties of the thermal    2625 1451
   constants and resonance paprameters were not considered these  2625 1451
   covariances are very conservative and should be considered as  2625 1451
   an upper limit of uncertainties.                               2625 1451
                                                                  2625 1451
   In the case of (n,2n) and (n,p) reaction where IRDFF cross     2625 1451
   sections were used in the evaluation procedure in place of the 2625 1451
   experimental datasets it was desirable to retain, as far as    2625 1451
   possible, also IRDFF covariances. We preserved KALMAN created  2625 1451
   covariances but during the procedure, we adjusted weights of   2625 1451
   the IRDFF cross sections to reproduce, as closely as possible, 2625 1451
   the original IRDFF uncertainties.                              2625 1451
